member.summary:
Parses the contents of a git config file and makes the sections, subsections, and variables accessible via Dictionaries.
Parsing follows the syntax specified at https://git-scm.com/docs/git-config
If a syntax violation is detected then an corresponding error will be populated in the ParsingErrors property.

Example instantiation:
    cfgFileContents = File.ReadAllText(".git\\config"));
    GitConfig gitCfg = new GitConfig(cfgFileContents);

Example section/variable access:
    // Print all settings under the [core] section.
    var coreSection = gitCfg.Sections["core"];
    foreach (var variable in coreSection.Variables)
    {
        Console.WriteLine($"{variable.Key} = {variable.Value}");
    }
